Package org.alljoyn.bus.annotation

This package contains the various annotations that are specific to AllJoyn.

See: Description

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    AccessPermission
    Indicates peer access permission requirement on the Method.
    BusAnnotation
    Bus Methods, Signals, Properties and Interfaces can all have Annotations, which have a name and a value
    BusAnnotations
    Bus Methods, Signals, Properties and Interfaces can all have Annotations, which have a name and a value
    BusInterface
    Indicates that a given Java interface is also an AllJoyn interface.
    BusMethod
    Indicates that a particular member of an AllJoyn exportable interface is defined to be a AllJoyn method.
    BusProperty
    Indicates that a particular member of an AllJoyn exportable interface is defined to be a AllJoyn property.
    BusSignal
    Indicates that a particular member of an AllJoyn exportable interface is defined to be a AllJoyn signal.
    BusSignalHandler
    Indicates that a method should receive AllJoyn signals.
    Position
    Indicates the numeric position of a field within an AllJoyn struct (Java class).
    Secure
    Indicates that a given interface is secured by an authentication mechanism.
    Signature
    Declares the AllJoyn data type of a Java data type.
